OL,6,FMr Scott told magistrates: "He's
OL,7,Fdestroyed a building. The choice today
OL,8,Fis whether or not his life is
OL,9,Fdestroyed as a result of that. I
OL,10,Fsubmit there's a risk of that
OL,11,Fhappening if he goes away."
OL,13,FChair of the Bench, John Fleet, asked
OL,14,Fthe youth if he wanted to say anything
OL,15,Fwhich may persuade them to hand him a
OL,16,Freferral order rather than a period in
OL,17,Fdetention.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/15
