OL,3,CTeens in custody after causing fire
OL,4,Cand #15m damage at Grade-listed hall
OL,6,F"I think we both sort of knew in the
OL,7,Fback of our minds that the fire
OL,8,Fbrigade were already on the phone. We
OL,9,Fcould hear shouting from outside,
OL,10,Fthat's where we found out where the
OL,11,Fwindow was to get out."
OL,13,FMr Fleet sentenced him to a six month
OL,14,Fdetention and training order.
OL,16,FAmy Lamb, defending the second youth,
OL,17,Ftold the court how he was studying A
OL,18,Flevels, had a part-time job and was
OL,19,Fhoping to go to university. She handed
OL,20,Fover a letter, which he had written
OL,21,Fhimself, to the bench.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G12/15
