OL,3,CTeens in custody after causing fire
OL,4,Cand #15m damage at Grade-listed hall
OL,6,F"In terms of mitigation he is a boy
OL,7,Fwho is genuinely sorry and remorseful
OL,8,Ffor his actions," she said. "His
OL,9,Fletter sets out deeply how mortified
OL,10,Fand remorseful he is to be here after
OL,11,Fcommitting his offence."
OL,13,FShe also told the bench: "At the time
OL,14,Fwhen it took hold he has tried to use
OL,15,Fa fire extinguisher, he'd been unable
OL,16,Fto make it work. He fully accepts that
OL,17,Fhe ran away from the scene in a panic.
OL,19,F"It was not his ambition at all to
OL,20,Fcause large scale damage."
